{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lindenmayer systems (also known as L-systems) are formalized rewriting tools used to create recursive fractals and organic shapes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The simplest form of an L-system uses a sequence of single characters, and a set of rules it applies to each element of the sequence, replacing it with one or more new elements."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The sequence of elements are then interpreted, often using a turtle graphics metaphor, into a visual representation."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This library implements a more advanced form L-system, known as a parametric, contextual L-system, inspired by book "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/algorithmicbotany.org\/papers\/abop\/abop.pdf"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The library includes types and protocols to support building your own Lindenmayer systems and a number examples sourced from "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/L-system"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/algorithmicbotany.org\/papers\/"},{"type":"text","text":" hosted at "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/algorithmicbotany.org\/"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While the simplest forms of L-systems use single characters, this library defines the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Module"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol, which represents one of the elements."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In addition to a number of built-in "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Modules"},{"type":"text","text":", you can define your own modules with properties that are made available to rewriting rules."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get support for using this package, see the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/heckj\/Lindenmayer\/discussions"},{"type":"text","text":" for questions and community feedback, or the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/heckj\/Lindenmayer\/issues"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":2,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/lindenmayer"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Lindenmayer provides a library to develop and run your own Lindenmayer Systems."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Library","externalID":"Lindenmayer","title":"Lindenmayer","symbolKind":"module","role":"collection","modules":[{"name":"Lindenmayer"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Lindenmayer systems","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/Creating_L-systems","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/LSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ContextualLSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RandomContextualLSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ParameterizedRandomContextualLSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/LindenmayerSystem","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ModuleSet","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/RNGWrapper","doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer\/ParametersWrapper"]},{"title":"Modules","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Lindenmayer\/documentation\/Lindenmayer